      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera remains a purist's benchmark, featuring the high-revving 3.6L flat-six engine mated to a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The hydraulic steering rack offers communicative feedback often lost in modern EPS systems. Essential preventative maintenance is addressed, including an upgraded IMS bearing and rear main seal. The chassis maintains its factory composure with active PASM dampers and precise turn-in. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the mechanical integrity is robust, supported by a clean over-rev report and verified compression. A driver-focused example with excellent throttle response and a linear power band.",
